Description: The rest on the flight into Egypt set in a border with vine and playing putti; the Virgin seated next to a tree in foreground, turned to left and looking at the infant Christ in her arms; St Joseph seated on the ground at far r, asleep; landscape background; the border also with putti pulling a cart at lower left; the lower right corner of the border made up, the border stained in various places; printed from one block. 1515 Woodcut
Curator's comments: BM also has another impression without the border, see E,9.78.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / German engravings, etchings and woodcuts c.1400-1700 (9)
Dodgson 1903, 1911 / Catalogue of Early German and Flemish Woodcuts in the BM, 2 vols (II.32.85a)
Acquisition notes: The print is laid down and there is no indication of the provenance on the mount.
